metadata.name: Reginald
metadata.description: In the city's heart lived Reginald, an elegant crocodile who favored urban life over the swamps. Dressed in his finest suit, he roamed the streets, relishing literature and the arts. With a passion for jazz, he joined a struggling band as their pianist. Reginald's piano skills soon became the talk of the town, and he found his true calling. He reveled in dazzling audiences, knowing he had found his place in the world as a refined crocodile with a talent for jazz, leaving his old life behind.
